counts.tsv`: columns `Reference`, then one per sample,\n    `write.table(..., sep='\\t', row.names=FALSE)`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/normalized_counts.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: normalized_counts.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"all_counts.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"all_counts.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"samples.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"samples.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/normalized_counts.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_tamglt28amkBdBzOV1abRqjw", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files `input/all_counts.tsv` and `input/samples.tsv`.\\n2. Load the DESeq2 library in R.\\n3. Create a DESeqDataSet object using the counts matrix and sample information with the design formula `~condition`.\\n4. Filter out rows where the total count is less than or equal to 10.\\n5. Run the DESeq function to perform differential expression analysis.\\n6. Save the DESeqDataSet object to `output/dds.rds`.\\n7. Extract normalized counts and write them to `output/normalized_counts.tsv`.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/normalized_counts.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (603 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_tamglt28amkBdBzOV1abRqjw"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_IeRgkysuLZtY8IyGpsjR8LDw", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"rela